entry.title: Covid-19 Herd Immunity Proves Elusive in U.K.
entry.content: In the summer, the U.K. lifted most restrictions in the hope that immunity would keep the virus at bay, but recent rises in cases and deaths indicate that reliance on this doesn’t guarantee a quick victory.

entry.title: Taliban Commander Who Launched Bombings in Kabul Is Now a Police Chief in Charge of Security
entry.content: Mawlawi Zubair Mutmaeen is one of thousands of former fighters thrown into mundane jobs as new government struggles to stay on its feet.
